djbdns is a collection of Domain Name System tools created by
Daniel J. Bernstein, focused on security and reliability.

Primary use case: authoritative DNS serving with tinydns.

Includes:
  * tinydns: fast, secure authoritative DNS server
  * tinydns-data: zone data compiler
  * axfrdns: DNS zone transfer server (optional)
  * rbldns: real-time blackhole list server
  * walldns: reverse DNS wall
  * pickdns: load-balancing DNS server
  * dnscache: caching recursive resolver (optional, not recommended
    for new deployments - consider dns/unbound instead)
  * DNS client utilities: dnsip, dnsname, dnsmx, dnstxt, dnsq, etc.

This port includes IPv6 support (Felix von Leitner's test32 patch),
security fixes (CVE-2008-4392, CVE-2009-0858, CVE-2012-1191), and
LP64 portability fixes. Patches are drawn from Gentoo, Debian, pkgsrc,
and Alpine Linux, all of which actively maintain djbdns packages.
